solution: ```class Solution:
    def checkSubarraySum(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> bool:
        rem = {0: -1}
        s = 0
        for i, v in enumerate(nums):
            s += v
            r = s % k if k else s
            if r in rem:
                if i - rem[r] > 1:
                    return True
            else:
                rem[r] = i
        return False
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(min(n, k))
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses prefix-sum modulo trick: store first index of each remainder; if same remainder appears later, the subarray between has sum divisible by k. Handles k=0 by treating it as a special case.

